@ENDNODE
@NODE reqments "Directory Opus 4 System Requirements"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Minimum System requirements@{ub}@{PAR}

To get Directory Opus 4 running you should have an Amiga computer with
at least AmigaOS 3.0. This computer should be equipped with a 68020
processor (or any later model of the 68xxx CPU series). DirOpus needs at
least 0.5 megabyte of memory.@{PAR}

@{FG Highlight}Recommended Third Party AddOns@{FG text}@{PAR}

Additional functionality can be achieved by installing the third party
libraries described below.@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

@{i}PopupMenu.library: @{ui}@{PAR}

This will enable the popup menu that appears by clicking on the
@{" Disk Name " link 1.5.2} field with the right mouse button. This library is
Freeware and can be found on Aminet (util/libs/pmuser.lha).@{PAR}

@{i}XADMaster.library: @{ui}@{PAR}

This is a depacker system that is used to handle various types of file archives from
within DOpus. With this library system installed, you can @{" browse through archives " link 1.11} as
if it were normal directories. This library is Shareware and can be found on Aminet
(util/arc/xadmaster.lha). It is also included with OS 3.9 (OS 3.9 users: Please read
the @{" FAQ " link faq} entry regarding XADmaster.library!!). See also: @{" FORCEOPENXAD " link 1.3.1} tooltype.@{PAR}

@{i}XFDMaster.library: @{ui}@{PAR}

This is a decruncher system that decompresses crunched files on
the fly. DirOpus utilizes this library to load such crunched files
(i.e. into the text viewer). This library is Freeware and can be
found on Aminet (util/pack/xfdmaster.lha). See also: @{" FORCEOPENXFD " link 1.3.1}
tooltype and @{" -x " link 1.3.2} argument.@{PAR}

@{i}SysInfo.library: @{ui}@{PAR}

DirOpus can use this library for CPU usage estimation (instead of internal
meter). This might result in a more accurate value. Note that the library requires
Executive or SysMon to work. If none of them is running DOpus falls back to
internal meter. SysInfo.library support must be turned on with the @{" USESYSINFO " link 1.3.1} tooltype.@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
@NODE installation "Installation"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Installing Directory Opus@{ub}@{PAR}

To install DirectoryOpus, just copy its directory to any place on your harddisk.@{PAR}

The program doesn't require any additional libraries to work, but there are several
recommended third party Add-Ons that will increase DOpus' functionality. Have a look at
the @{" Requirements " link reqments} section for more information.@{PAR}

Beginning with version 4.16, Directory Opus does not need an assign anymore.
If you are upgrading from earlier versions of the program, check your
"User-Startup" file located in S: and remove the following line:@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

ASSIGN DOPUS: <path to your old version of DOpus>@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 1}

(where "<path to...>" would be something like "SYS:Tools/Dopus").@{PAR}

@{FG highlight}Further notes regarding installation@{FG text}@{PAR}

If you're upgrading from a very old version (3.x or earlier) or you used to
have your DirOpus files spread around your harddisk, please make sure that
the following files do not exist in your system directories (you may encounter
various problems otherwise):@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

DopusRT:           C:@{PAR}
ConfigOpus#?       C:@{PAR}
DOpus_#?           C:@{PAR}
Diskcopy.info      C:@{PAR}
Format.info        C:@{PAR}
Install.info       C:@{PAR}
dopus.library      LIBS:@{PAR}
DirectoryOpus.#?   S:@{PAR}
DO_Deutsch.#?      S:@{PAR}
ConfigOpus.#?      S:@{PAR}
CO_Deutsch.#?      S:@{PAR}
DM_#?_Deutsch.str  S:@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 1}

@ENDNODE
