@NODE GetAll  "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}GetAll  [SEPARATOR]  [WIN]@{ub}@{PAR}

@{" ARexx Only " link ComRefInf 8}@{PAR}


   SEPARATOR  optional; character used to separate names@{PAR}

         WIN  optional; window to get names from@{PAR}
              (-1 = current window, 0 = left or 1 = right)@{PAR}
              defaults to -1.@{PAR}


This command returns, in the RESULT variable, the names of all
entries in the active directory window (or the specified window). If
SEPARATOR is specified, the names are separated by a separator. The
default separator is a space. You should be prepared to handle a long
string.@{PAR}


