@NODE Hunt "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Hunt  [NAME]  [PATTERN]@{ub}@{PAR}


      NAME  optional; name of directory to hunt@{PAR}

   PATTERN  optional; file pattern to hunt@{PAR}


This command allows you to search all selected directories (and
their sub-directories for a specified file or files. A requester
appears asking for the pattern to hunt for. You can use full pattern
matching for this search.@{PAR}

If a file matching the pattern is found, you are asked if you wish
to enter the directory containing it, or continue the search. If you
elect to enter the directory, the directory will be read and then all
matching entries will be highlighted.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

