@NODE Play "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Play  [NAME]@{ub}@{PAR}


   NAME  optional; name of file@{PAR}


This will attempt to play each selected file. If the file is an
8SVX format IFF sampled sound (of the type generated by AudioMaster,
for instance), the speed and other information from within the file
will be used. The Play routine plays both mono and stereo IFF 8SVX
files. When playing a file that is not IFF 8SVX, it will assume a
speed of 10000 samples/second.@{PAR}

This command also plays song modules. See @{" PlayST " link PlayST} for more
information.@{PAR}

Each file is played once only, unlike the @{" LoopPlay " link LoopPlay} command,
which plays each file continuously.@{PAR}

If the System/View/Play/Turn audio filter off for play option is
selected, the high-pass audio filter will be turned off while a sound
is playing.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
@NODE PlayST "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}PlayST  [NAME]@{ub}@{PAR}


   NAME  optional; name of file@{PAR}


Play a song module. Directory Opus supports
Sound/Noise/ProTracker, Oktalizer and MED modules.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
