@NODE Rename "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Rename  [NAME] [NEWNAME]@{ub}@{PAR}


      NAME  optional; name of file@{PAR}

   NEWNAME  optional; newname to give to selected file@{PAR}


This allows you to rename all selected files and directories. You
may use a * to specify a pattern. If no * is used, you are asked for a
new name for each individual file.@{PAR}

To add a prefix or a suffix (or both) to all selected entries, use
a * in the second string field. For example, to add HIRES as a prefix
and .pic as a suffix to all selected entries, enter HIRES*.pic.@{PAR}

To change a prefix or a suffix (or both) on all selected entries,
use a * in the top string field. For example, to change HIRES to
MEDRES as a prefix, and.pic to .iff as a suffix, enter HIRES*.pic in
the top string field, and MEDRES*.iff in the bottom string field.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
