@NODE ScanDir "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}ScanDir  PATH  [WIN]@{ub}@{PAR}


   PATH  path to read@{PAR}

    WIN  optional; window to read directory into@{PAR}
         (-1 = current window, 0=left or 1=right)@{PAR}
         defaults to -1.@{PAR}


This command allows you to read a directory in much the same way
as the drive buttons. For example:@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

Command ScanDir Dh0:work@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 1}

would read the DH0:Work directory into the current window.@{PAR}

One usage of this allows you to have an entire bank of buttons
devoted to "drive buttons". You could then set up a button on every
other bank that would, using the @{" Modify " link Modify} command, jump to that bank.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
