@NODE SetVar "Tech Guide/Commands"
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}SetVar  VARIABLE  CONTENT@{ub}@{PAR}


 VARIABLE  name of the internal variable@{PAR}

  CONTENT  content of the variable@{PAR}


This command lets you create internal variables and define their content. These variables
can later on be reffered with the {v} @{" argument function " link SimArgFun}. It's
difficult to explain, so here's an example:@{PAR}

Create a button called "Remember dir" and define its action like this:@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

COMMAND:  SetVar RememberedDir {s}@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 1}

Create another button called "Restore dir" and define its action like this:@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 4}

COMMAND:  ScanDir {vRememberedDir}@{PAR}
@{LINDENT 1}

The first button will "remember" the directory displayed in the currently active directory
window: It will store its path in the internal variable "RememberedDir".@{PAR}

The second button will allow you to switch back to that directory at any time. It invokes the
@{" ScanDir " link ScanDir} command with the internal variable "RememberedDir" as an argument.@{PAR}


ARexx Results:@{PAR}

@{" RC " link ComRefInf 24} = 0@{PAR}

@{" Result " link ComRefInf 24} = undefined@{PAR}

@ENDNODE
